@Nancy 
During the late 1960's, I worked part-time in the hosiery dept. at B. Altman's in Manhattan.  I attended college classes in the morning and spent my afternoons and Saturday at the store.  We sold stockings and pantyhose - Hanes.

I remember slipping the back of my hand into the stocking so the customer could see the shade against my skin.  That's a pleasant memory for me.  B Altman was a special store where we were treated well.  I never spent my paycheck there, even with a discount, because the items were too expensive, but the store had an employee cafeteria that served excellent food at very low prices. That helped out a lot.  There was good in some of those "good old days."

